<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.11.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#8">National Parks</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.11.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80267" speakername="Mary Scanlon (Highlands and Islands) (Con)" spid="S2W-9717" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#8">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what action is being taken to ensure that Scottish Water&rsquo;s investment programme in the Cairngorms National Park will not have an adverse impact on housing development.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.11.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80032" speakername="Ross Finnie" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#8">

  <p>Any investment proposed by Scottish Water within the Cairngorms National Park would be subject to the same planning controls as would apply to any other organisation intending to develop there. The Cairngorms National Park Authority also has call in powers on any planning application made in its area.</p>

  <p>The extent to which Scottish Water&rsquo;s current investment programme is constraining development in any part of Scotland is an operational matter for Scottish Water. However, I launched on 20 July public consultations on Scottish Water&rsquo;s next investment programme (<em>Investing in Water Services 2006-2014</em>) and future charging policies (<em>Paying for Water Services 2006-2010</em>). These consultations provide an important opportunity for all affected parties to make their views known on the future investment priorities and who should pay for them.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.12.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#9">School Meals</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.12.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80023" speakername="Frances Curran (West of Scotland) (SSP)" spid="S2W-9622" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#9" holdingdate="2004-08-03">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many education authorities have introduced multiple-use cards for school meal applications in secondary schools.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.12.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80105" speakername="Euan Robson" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#9">

  <p>This information is not collected centrally. In June 2004, the Executive published the annual school meal census report, the results of which indicated that 26% of mainstream schools in Scotland operated an anonymised system for free school meal receipt.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.13.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#10">Scottish Deprivation Index</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.13.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80000" speakername="Brian Adam (Aberdeen North) (SNP)" spid="S2W-8903" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#10" holdingdate="2004-06-23">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive on what basis the basic building block of the Scottish Deprivation Index will be assessed and when the assessment will be published.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2004-08-11.13.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80022" speakername="Ms Margaret Curran" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-04/wa0811.htm#10">

  <p>The Scottish Index of Multiple Deprivation 2004 was published on 14 June 2004.</p>

  <p>The Index is based on the data zone geography and includes indicators from the following domains Current Income, Employment, Education, Skills and Training, Health, Housing and Geographic Access and Telecommunications.</p>

</reply>


